-- Lukoil, TNK-BP Ask Putin for Offshore Oil Access, Interfax Says
-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a
-- 2012-04-12T10:46:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-12/lukoil-tnk-bp-ask-putin-for-offshore-oil-access-interfax-says.html
Russia ’s largest non-state oil
companies urged Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin  to expand access
to the country’s offshore deposits, currently only open to
state-run OAO Rosneft and OAO Gazprom, Interfax reported.  OAO Lukoil, TNK-BP, OAO Surgutneftegas and OAO Bashneft are
seeking permission to develop Russia’s continental shelf, the
news service said, citing a copy of a letter to Putin.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anna Shiryaevskaya in Moscow at 
